{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/scaling3dScale","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/viewport\/scaling3dscale"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"scaling3dScale"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using FSR upscaling, AMD recommends exposing the following values as preset options to users “Ultra Quality: 0.77”, “Quality: 0.67”, “Balanced: 0.59”, “Performance: 0.5” instead of exposing the entire scale."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To control this property on the root viewport, set the "},{"code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/scaling3d\/scale","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" project setting.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Scales the 3D render buffer based on the viewport size uses an image filter specified in ","type":"text"},{"code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/scaling3d\/mode","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to scale the output image to the full viewport size. Values lower than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"text":" can be used to speed up 3D rendering at the cost of quality (undersampling). Values greater than ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" are only valid for bilinear mode and can be used to improve 3D rendering quality at a high performance cost (supersampling). See also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/antiAliasing\/quality\/msaa3d"},{"type":"text","text":" for multi-sample antialiasing, which is significantly cheaper but only smooths the edges of polygons."}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot8ViewportC14scaling3dScaleSdvp","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"scaling3dScale","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","symbolKind":"property","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"role":"symbol","title":"scaling3dScale"},"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"title":"SwiftGodot","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","role":"collection","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Viewport/scaling3dScale":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"scaling3dScale","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Double","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/viewport\/scaling3dscale","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/scaling3dScale","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Scales the 3D render buffer based on the viewport size uses an image filter specified in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/scaling3d\/mode"},{"type":"text","text":" to scale the output image to the full viewport size. Values lower than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"text":" can be used to speed up 3D rendering at the cost of quality (undersampling). Values greater than ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"text":" are only valid for bilinear mode and can be used to improve 3D rendering quality at a high performance cost (supersampling). See also ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/rendering\/antiAliasing\/quality\/msaa3d"},{"type":"text","text":" for multi-sample antialiasing, which is significantly cheaper but only smooths the edges of polygons."}],"title":"scaling3dScale","role":"symbol"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Viewport":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Viewport","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Viewport","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/viewport","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Viewport","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Abstract base class for viewports. Encapsulates drawing and interaction with a game world.","type":"text"}]}}}